<fieldset id="preface">
  <legend>Preface</legend>
  <p>The Obsolete Air-Cooled Documentation Project presents
     out-of-print technical resources online for use by the
     air-cooled enthusist community. For more information about
     this project and it's purpose, please visit
     the <a href="aboutdoc.html">about</a> page, which includes
     our <a href="aboutdoc.html#legal">legal</a> statement.</p>

  <p><b>Notice:</b> other websites embed portions of this
     site, so if you have questions, comments, or out-of-print
     material you'd like to see here please use the contact
     information shown on our <a href="contact.html">contact</a>
     page.</p>

  <p>The documents on this site are represented in png,
     pdf, jpeg, and a few other file formats.  If a file
     type isn't useable by your system, please visit
     the <a href="utilities.html">utilities</a> page to find
     useful programs for your operating system of choice.</p> 
	
  <p>If you're interested in mirroring the site, please visit
     the <a href="mirroring.html">mirroring</a> page, which
     describes methods to keep a local, up to date version of the
     OACDP.</p>

</fieldset>

<fieldset id="documents">
  <legend>The Documents</legend>
  <ol id="documentList">
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="wog69.html" id="wog69">Without Guesswork 1969</a>
        <p class="desc">
          Technical data for workshop use, covers December 1953 through
          August 1968 (1969 model year), types 1, 2, and 3.
          Contains measurements, clearances, wear limits,
          performance data, etc -- lots of details for the detail
          people!  155 pages.
        </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="wog72.html" id="wog72">Without Guesswork 1972</a>
      <p class="desc">
        Technical data for workshop use, covers August 1970 (1971
        model year) through October 1972 (1973 model year), types
        1, 2, 3, and 4, models imported to USA and Canada.
        Contains measurements, clearances, wear limits,
        performance data, etc -- lots of details for the detail
        people!  157 pages.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="5054part.html" id="part5054">
        Type II VW Parts Reference (1950-1954)
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
        For "Barndoor" (large engine lid) split-window busses,
        this manual contains diagrams and part numbers
        for <b>every single</b> part on the bus, including the
        special variants like the ambulance and pickup. 530
        pages. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="5867part.html" id="part5867">
        Type II VW Parts Reference (1958-1967)
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
        For post-barndoor era split-window busses, this manual
        contains diagrams and part numbers for <b>every single</b>
        part on the bus, including the special variants like the
        ambulance and pickup.  750 pages.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="progref4061.html" id="progref4061">
	Progressive Refinements (1940-1961)
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
	An internal VW book that documents the incremental changes to
	type 1/2/3 VWs from early production in 1940 until 1961.  150
	pages.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="progref6268.html" id="progref6268">
	Progressive Refinements (1962-1968)
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
	An internal VW book that documents the incremental changes to
	type 1/2/3 VWs from 1962 until 1961. 98 pages.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc" id="so42">
      <a href="so42.html">SO-42 Camper Parts List</a>
      <p class="desc">
        A parts list for the split-window SO-42 camper. I think
        that is all it covers, but I could be wrong.  Please let
        me know about missing information as well.  58 pages.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="solex.html" id="solex">
        Solex: Selection and Tuning of the Carburetor
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
        This manual from Solex describes how to calculate the
        correct size of carburetor for an engine (not just VW
        engines), and how to determine the correct jet sizes and
        settings. 46 pages.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="tools.html" id="tools">
        Local Manufacture of Workshop Equipment
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
        This manual contains descriptions and blueprints for
        over 100 special tools for working on air-cooled VWs --
        everything from a body trolley for Type 1s to a
        headlight bucket alignment jig for Type 34s. January
        1959 edition, updated to September 1967.  381 pages.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="damage.html" id="damage">
        Damage Numbers (1965 ed.)
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
	This manual was used by dealers to report the reasons they
	replaced Type 1, 2, or 3 parts under warranty.  For parts
	that could come from more than one supplier, it shows how
	to identify the supplier via logo or other marking.  It
	also has a section on sealing Type 1 and Type 3 bodies - I
	guess Buses didn't leak! 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="ebersp.html" id="ebersp">
        Workshop Manual: Fresh Air Heaters
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
        This manual covers Eberspacher gas heaters installed in
        several types of air-cooled Volkswagens. These units are
        relatively unsafe if not well looked after, so hopefully
        owners of these heaters will find this information
        useful. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li class="doc">
      <a href="ba4.html" id="ba4">
        Troubleshooting Guide: BA-4 Gas Heaters
      </a>
      <p class="desc">
        This manual covers troubleshooting of the BA-4 gas heater.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
